title: Grateful Dead Live at Club Melk Weg on 1981-10-16
description:
Set I
Acoustic Set

On The Road Again
Dire Wolf
Monkey & The Engineer
Bird Song
Cassidy
Oh Babe It Ain't No Lie
The Race is On
Ripple
Set II
Electric Set

Playing In The Band >
Hully Gully >
The Wheel >
Samson & Delilah
Gloria >
Turn On Your Lovelight >
Goin' Down The Road Feeling Bad >
Playing In The Band Reprise >
Black Peter >
Sugar Magnolia

 
Comment
Set I is Bobby and Jerry playing acoustic on borrowed instruments.

Cindy Poris opened
No encore performed

Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Brent Mydland - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums

reviews.review_text:
bobbys birthday show with the exception of Phil's bass, all the gear played on is borrowed.
Bobby in fine birthday mode busts out some old time favorites like Hully Gully, Lovelight and Gloria.

Simply astounding! An exceptional treasure to marvel at. I love how at the end, instead of an encore they give gratitude. Afterall they are the Grateful Dead, so giving thanks just seems natural. The Doug’s is crisp & clean throughout, their playing is just so elevated. Love the acoustic set. This club seems so small and intimate, the audience got so rewarded with a killer show. When was the last time Lovelight was performed? Such a unique show they were on and psyched to be there you can hear it in their playing. This matrix mix is superb!
